data.title: The Power of 'No': A Spiritual Guide to Your Season of 'Yes'
data.description: I never liked the word "no". In fact, my father often told me that, as a child, he was fascinated by the fact that I rarely used the term as an act of rebellion like most children did. The word "no" has always conjured negative and self-deprecating feelings in me and, so, I avoided it like a plague, whether hearing it used by others, or in my own vocabulary. Nevertheless, after several years of being a professional actress I have changed my relationship with a word I once feared the most. I did this by recognizing the immense value of “No” and the favorable power it can bring to my life.

data.title: From Awareness to Reinforcement Through Conscious Change
data.description:
I was told I was terrible at "dealing with ambiguity". How could this be? My whole career as a Project and Process manager was dealing with ambiguity. This started me on my journey towards a career in Change Management. I learned the “missing link” present in all changes and most importantly, where to focus when change isn't happening.

70% of Change Initiatives fail! We see it in our daily lives (“I keep forgetting to have a mask ready when we get deliveries and then have to go running around in a panic!”) and at work (trouble introducing new IT tools, processes, transformations, re-organizations, etc.). As a change manager, I ensure people adopt change while reducing resistance, resulting in increased productivity, engagement, and return on investments. I'm on a mission to improve leadership for a better world!

During this chat, I’ll share the following:

  • What a career in Change Management looks like
  • The framework of successful change for people AND organizations
  • Easy secrets for making change work for you

data.title: How These Women are Influencing Diversity Initiatives for Latinas at this Investment Firm
data.description:
If you’ve ever hesitated to look at financial services as a career option for diverse women, be prepared to be pleasantly surprised. Meet three Hispanic women at different stages of their career with T. Rowe Price as they share their experiences and what has changed for Latinas in the workplace. They will be joined by a senior member of the firm’s Diversity & Inclusion team and together, they will tackle topics such as:

  • How to foster a stronger sense of culture
  • How to differentiate yourself as a leader
  • The importance of getting involved in D&I efforts at your workplace

data.title: Living Abroad as a Black Woman: Finding the Freedom to Thrive
data.description:
When I left the U.S. to move to Spain 6 years ago, I had no idea the impact that it would have... not only on my life but on the lives of other Black women around the world and for generations to come. Living abroad as a Black woman has taught me so much about myself, my history, my future, and the impact that it can have for those to come after me. When we learn how to rewrite our stories, on our own terms... that's when real change happens.

In this chat, I'll share with you...

  • The impact that living in a different country has on life and those to come
  • How to find professional opportunities abroad and build personal relationships
  • Why freedom and flexibility are the keys to coping with racial injustice

data.title: OFFICE HOURS: Personal Finance 101: Take Charge of Your Financial Life for a Better Tomorrow
data.description:
There was a time when I was genuinely overwhelmed and intimidated by the topic of finance. However, I faced my fears and began taking baby steps. Quickly I actually began to enjoy learning about this topic. The more I learned, the easier it became to take concrete steps. Soon after, I was able to share my passion with others (including developing and hosting a well-received financial literacy webinar at my workplace).

So if you're intimidated by finance and are not sure where to start, this personal finance 101 chat is for you!

During this chat:

  • I want to share with you the importance of taking charge of your financial life
  • You will be able to take actionable steps to start investing
  • You will start laying a strong financial foundation for a better tomorrow
